comments.body:
Interesting.

This makes code that uses a raw `Icon` look kinda weird. For example:

``` dart
  @override
  Widget buildChild() {
    return new ListItem(
      enabled: config.enabled,
      leading: new FadeTransition(
        opacity: _opacity,
        child: _controller.isDismissed ? null : Icons.done
      ),
      title: config.child
    );
  }
```

It's not obvious that `Icons.done` is a Widget.

I dunno. We should decide one way or the other on this before I land because it affects what code gets broken (either way it's a backwards-incompatible change).
